The paper discusses the integration of cloud-based artificial intelligence and machine learning into the transportation system, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). It also emphasizes the role of AI in data processing, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses security and privacy issues associated with the proposed architecture, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the proposed architecture on the transportation system, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
